For this task, I used Canva to create a digital literacy awareness infographic aimed at helping students better understand how to use technology effectively and responsibly. Canva was chosen because it is user-friendly and provides a wide range of templates, icons, and design elements that support the creation of visually engaging content for free.
The infographic is a one-page design that explains the concept of digital literacy and emphasizes its importance for students. It includes key sections such as what digital literacy is, why it matters, useful digital tools, safe internet practices, and email etiquette. Each section presents concise explanations along with practical tips for example, creating strong passwords and recognizing unreliable websites to help students apply these skills in real-life situations. Clear headings, icons, and structured spacing were used to make the information easy to read and visually appealing.
One challenge I faced was organizing a large amount of information into a single page without making the design look cluttered. To overcome this, I used one the canva's template which I thought was suitable to integrate these informations.
